BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
We can use whatever values for [`x`] that we like, as long as they are all different. The equation tells us the [`y`]-value has to be [`-4.25`] each time.

>> [@DataTable(
  [
    [[PGML('[`x`]'),
      rowbottom => '2',
      midrule => '1',],
     PGML('[`y`]'),
    ],
    [PGML('[`-2`]'),
     PGML('[`-4.25`]'),
    ],
    [PGML('[`-1`]'),
     PGML('[`-4.25`]'),
    ],
    [PGML('[`0`]'),
     PGML('[`-4.25`]'),
    ],
    [PGML('[`1`]'),
     PGML('[`-4.25`]'),
    ],
    [PGML('[`2`]'),
     PGML('[`-4.25`]'),
    ],
  ],
      align => 'cc',
      valign => 'middle',);@]* <<

